HEADWORD: methylenedioxymethamphetamine
<hw>methylenedioxymethamphetamine</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a drug
designed to have the effects of amphetamines but to avoid the drug laws,
but now a controlled substance. Called also
<altname>MDMA</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> MDMA, Adam, ecstasy.</syn>⟦br⟧
